{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πολιός</b>, ά, όν, <br /> also ός, όν, ἁλὸς πολιοῖο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 20.229, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.410, etc.; χήραν πολιόν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Andromache” 348 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>grey, grizzled, grisly,</b> λύκοιο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 10.334; κορῶναι 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 967; σίδηρος 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 9.366, “hymnus ad Mercurium” 41, compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 758 (Lyric poetry) \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of the surging sea, πολιῆς ἐπὶ θινὶ θαλάσσης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 4.248; πολιὴν ἅλα ναιέμεν 15.190; π. θάλασσα 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 51; π. πέλαγος 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Aves” 350 (Lyric poetry); γάλα 4th c.AD(?): Quintus Smyrnaeus Epicus 10.135; λύκοι 1G 42(1).131.12 (Epid.)\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; but, <br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> most frequently of human hair, <b>grey</b> from age, κάρη, κεφαλή, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.74, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.317, etc.; π. στῆθος 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus “Supp.” 20.2; γῆρας π. 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 6(5).15, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 258; πολιοί \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]<b>greyhaired men,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 24.499; π. ματέρες 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 182 (Lyric poetry), compare 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 35, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 600, 610, 692, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Parmenides” 127b (rare in _Attic dialect_ Prose), 3rd c.BC: Callimachus Epicus “Fragmenta” 473; Τραῖαι, ἐκ γενετῆς πολιαί 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Theogonia” 271 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: <i>comparative</i> <b>-ώτεροι</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Fragmenta” 235: _absolutely_, πολιαί (i.e. τρίχες) 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 4.28, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “de Generatione Animalium” 722a7, “Pr.” 898a31; πολιῶν ἔσχηκας τὸν πώγωνα μεστόν 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 2.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἅμα ταῖς π. κατιούσαις as the <b>grey hairs</b> come down (i. e. from the temples to the beard), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 520, compare 908; ἕως τὸ δὴ λεγόμενον πολιὰς σχῇ “PMich.Zen.” 77 (3rd c.BC),cf. LXX.Isa.47.2, +others, 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “περὶ κακιῶν ί” p.32J. \">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> τίς σε πολιᾶς ἐξανῆκε γαστρό; what <b>old woman's</b> womb bare thee? as a sarcasm, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.98 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; π. δάκρυον ἐκβάλλων <b>an old man's</b> tear, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 1209 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__3.b</b></Level4> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>hoary, venerable,</b> ὃς πολιῷ νόμῳ αἶσαν ὀρθοῖ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 673 (Lyric poetry); κληδὼν ἐν πολιαῖσι μένει φήμαις 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 701 (Lyric poetry); μάθημα χρόνῳ π. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Timaeus” 22b; πλοῦτος.. χρόνῳ π. 4th c.AD: Julianus Imperator “Orationes” 2.82b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>bright, clear, serene,</b> ἔαρ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 477, 492; αἰθήρ 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Orestes” 1376 (Lyric poetry); ἠήρ 3rd c.BC: Apollonius Rhodius Epicus 3.275, 4th c.AD(?): Quintus Smyrnaeus Epicus 2.554. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G8845","accentedUnicode":"πολιός","shortDef":"gray hair","mediumDef":"gray hair","stepGloss":"gray hair","stepTransliteration":"polios","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}